==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Immature
<hw>Im`ma*ture"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>immaturus</ets>; pref. <ets>im-</ets> not + <ets>maturus</ets>
mature, ripe. See <er>Mature</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Not mature;
unripe; not arrived at perfection of full development; crude;
unfinished; <as>as, <ex>immature</ex> fruit; <ex>immature</ex>
character; <ex>immature</ex> plans.</as></def> ⟦ldquo⟧An ill-measured
and <xex>immature</xex> counsel.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Premature; untimely; too early; <as>as, an immature
death</as>.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Jer. Taylor.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Immatured</ent>⟦br⟧
